song.title: The Solitude

annotations:
I never viewed
 The solitude
 As something to avoid until you left

Before partnership one tends to believe that solitude is not something to be feared or avoided. However, after having loved, the concept of being alone or single becomes quite distasteful. As the common saying goes “you don’t know what you have until it’s gone”.

Like baby when you’re gone
 The night’s too quiet
 Dinner table
 It’s one sided
 Too many pillows
 Too big a bed
 Can’t decide where to lay my head

Now with her lover gone she begins to notice changes within her day-to-day life. The quietness of her home and dinner table arrangement shows that she is alone, possibly reminiscing when her and her lover lived together. The fact that her bed has “Too many pillows” yet she cant decide where to rest her head shows how she is longing for her partners company and affection.
